    dc:creator "Oanh, Le Thi Kieu; Boyko, Christopher B." ;
    dc:date "2020" ;
    dc:title "Cancrion khanhensis sp. nov. (Crustacea: Isopoda: Entoniscidae) infesting Monomia haanii (Stimpson, 1858) (Crustacea: Brachyura: Portunidae) from Nha Trang Bay, Khanh Hoa, Vietnam, with remarks on larval stages of entoniscids and description of a new family, genus and two new species of hyperparasites" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4315903>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4315889>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4315891>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4315893>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4315895>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4315905> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4315903>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. A, Cancrion khanhensis sp. nov. mature ovigerous female; B, C. khanhensis sp. nov. mature female showing dorsolateral ovarian processes (arrows); C, C. khanhensis sp. nov, immature female (stage 8); D, C. khanhensis sp. nov. mature female infested by Stellatoniscus tentaculus gen. nov., sp. nov. mature female; E, S. tentaculus gen. nov., sp. nov. immature females (stage III); F, S. tentaculus gen. nov., sp. nov. mature female (stage IV). Scale bars = 5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4315903/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4315889>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Female of Cancrion khanhensis sp. nov. A, mature female (stage 12) in host sheath, lateral view (1, bulbous heart); B, mature female (stage 12), cephalon (1, outer antenna; 2, inner antenna; 3, coxopodite; 4, exopodite of maxilliped); C, mature female (stage 12), oostegite 1; D, mature female (stage 12) abdomen with pleural lamellae (1, distal end of pleon; 2, pleural lamella 2; 3, pleural lamella 1); E, pre-asticot female (immediately post-molt from cryptoniscus); F, pre-asticot female, more developed (stage 2); G, immature female (stage 5) with rudimentary pleural lamellae; H, immature female (stage 8) with moderately developed pleural lamellae (1, anterior lobe of oostegite 1 extending anterodorsal to cephalon; 2, oostegite 2; 3, pereopod 3; 4, pereopods 6 and 7; 5, heart). Stages find Kuris et al. (1980). Scale bars: A, C, D, G, H = 5 mm; B, E, F = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4315889/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4315891>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Mature male of Cancrion khanhensis sp. nov. A, habitus, ventral view; B, cephalon and pereomere 1, ventral view; C, dorsolateral view showing fusion of cephalon and pereomere 1; D, pereopod 1; E, pleomere 5 and pleotelson. Scale bars: A = 1 mm; B, C = 0.2 mm; D, E = 0.1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4315891/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4315893>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Epicaridium larva of Cancrion khanhensis sp. nov. A, habitus, ventral view; B, pereopod 6. Scale bars: 50 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4315893/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4315895>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Cryptoniscus larva of Cancrion khanhensis sp. nov. A, habitus, ventral view, dashed lines indicate missing parts; B, pereopod 1; C, pleopod 1; D, left uropod. Scale bars: A = 100 µm; B, C, D = 10 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4315895/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4315905>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. A, Uninfested Monomia haani; B, infested M. haani showing more highly vaulted carapace; C, ventral view of M. haanii carapace showing ovigerous female Cancrion khanhensis sp. nov. (arrow); D, double infestation of C. khanhensis sp. nov. (arrows). Scale bars: 1 cm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4315905/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

